From be19c5f7be726c4b009c20b088d9b4c357371a77 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: lutong <lutong14@huawei.com>
Date: Fri, 5 Jun 2026 17:28:40 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] mm/hugetlb: preparatory refactoring for hugetlb swap
 support

This is a combined preparatory series that lays the groundwork for
hugetlb page swap support. The changes include:

1) Move HPAGEFLAGS into a tail-page slot clear of folio->swap, so that
   the swap field can be safely used for hugetlb pages without conflict.

2) Compile out the huge_pmd_unshare path in rmap.c when
   CONFIG_HUGETLB_PMD_PAGE_TABLE_SHARING is disabled, reducing dead
   code and avoiding unnecessary locking overhead.

3) Factor out __hugetlb_add_to_page_cache() that accepts an
   already-locked folio, making it reusable for swap-in paths where
   the folio lock is held externally.

4) Expose hugetlb fault helper functions and extract
   hugetlb_fault_reserve() so they can be reused by the swap fault
   handling code.

5) Prepare the fault reclaim path for swap by renaming
   try_hugetlb_reclaim_notify() to try_hugetlb_fault_reclaim() and
   adjusting its interface. Add hugetlbfs_mapping() helper and exclude
   hugetlbfs mappings from shadow entry tracking in
   mapping_set_update().

Signed-off-by: nashzhou <zhouhaipeng13@huawei.com>
